        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 5<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>In 5 or 6 days I shall have my M.S (except last chapter which is partly written) ready to send to Printers; &amp; all wood-blocks, except for one of later chapters are complete.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Please inform me whether my servant shall leave the M.S (with letters of instructions) at M<hi rend="superscript">ss</hi> Clowes<ref target="#foot.f3"/> or to you.— I shall be ready to begin correcting Slips on the 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>, after a short absence from home for rest.—<ref target="#foot.f4"/></p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>Do you know anything about M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Clowes works in hand—will they be able to keep me steadily at work—it drives me mad to change from job to job.—</p>
<p>I ought to begin, at once, for I am a fearfully slow corrector &amp; always liable to interruptions from illness.—</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.1 5] <hi rend="italic">over</hi> ‘4’ </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">2.2 Slips] <hi rend="italic">above del</hi> ‘Revises’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
            
